Figure 1c schematically shows a configuration that enables sub-ambient passive radiative cooling using a directional approach. The proposed concept comprises an emitter in thermal communication with the atmosphere and a reflector that blocks direct-solar radiation. The emitter is enclosed within a readily available cover that is partially transparent in the atmospheric window and partially reflective in the solar spectrum to minimize heat gain due to diffuse-solar radiation. The overall cooling power of the emitter (per area) Pcooling at a temperature T can be estimated by accounting for all contributions to the energy balance:1PcoolingT=PradT-PatmTamb-Psolar-direct-Psolar-diffuse-PreflTrefl-Pcond-convT,Tamb\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
